= lesson 29: intermission 3

You've learned 131 words, and all the important grammar! So what now?

#strong[Join a Toki Pona community!] [ma pona](https://discord.gg/6zkugJFU4x)
and [kama sona](https://discord.gg/ChC6qtVsSE) are great places to find people
to talk to, and to practice. You can even [hang out in
VRChat](https://vrc.group/TOKI.9663)!

#strong[Stay informed!] Every two-four weeks we post a
[newsletter](https://sin-kulupu.pona.la/) about new things happening. Sign up so
you don't miss cool events, like the [24 hour celebration
stream](https://suno.pona.la/) we have every August!

#strong[Listen to spoken Toki Pona!] [kalama
sin](https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLjOmpMyMxd8Qs2mAXcLk817tQy_AQj09u)
is a podcast where you can listen to live conversations between proficient Toki
Pona speakers. Turn on subtitles if it's difficult to keep up!

#strong[Read more Toki Pona!]
[Practice](https://raacz.neocities.org/toki-pona/beginner-material) by reading
~70 short stories by jan Lakuse. [lipu tenpo](https://liputenpo.org/) publishes
a new zine every month or two, with short stories and talks.

And finally, #strong[listen to [Toki Pona music](https://kute.pona.la/)!] We
have lots of talented musicians writing original songs or translating songs they
love. Let's check out this awesome song #emph['ale li ante'] by jan Nikoleta
(kqa)!

